Reasoning: The paper deals with capacity problems in multiple-access scenarios with cooperative transmitters, which is a topic related to information theory and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the transmission of common information, which falls under the sub-category cs.COMM (Communication and Networking). Additionally, the paper deals with partial and perfect channel state information, which is related to network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper studies a specific two-transmitter/one-receiver scenario, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
